
Walk me through how ArgoCD syncs a Helm chart change from a PR merge to production.


ArgoCD Helm Chart Sync: PR Merge to Production
The Full Flow
1. PR Merge triggers CI

Developer merges a PR that bumps a value in values.yaml (e.g., image tag v1.2.3 → v1.2.4)
CI pipeline (GitHub Actions / GitLab CI) runs: lint, unit tests, helm template | kubeval to validate rendered manifests
Artifacts stay in Git — no direct cluster interaction from CI
2. ArgoCD detects the change

ArgoCD polls the Git repo every ~3 minutes by default (or receives a webhook push for near-instant detection)
It re-renders the Helm chart using the new values and compares the output against the live cluster state
Status flips from Synced to OutOfSync
3. Sync decision

Auto-sync on: ArgoCD immediately applies the diff — kubectl apply of only the changed resources
Auto-sync off: operator manually triggers argocd app sync <app> or approves via UI
4. Helm rendering happens inside ArgoCD

ArgoCD runs helm template server-side using the chart + values from the repo
It does NOT use helm install/upgrade — it converts Helm output to plain Kubernetes manifests and manages them with its own apply engine
This is why helm list won't show ArgoCD-managed releases by default
5. Apply and health check

ArgoCD applies the diff to the target namespace
It watches resource health: Deployment → ReplicaSet → Pods become Running
Once all resources are Healthy, app status returns to Synced + Healthy
6. Rollback

If the new version breaks health checks, ArgoCD marks it Degraded
Rollback = revert the commit in Git → ArgoCD syncs back to the previous state
No imperative helm rollback needed — Git history IS the rollback mechanism